Nasopharyngeal-aspirate and sputum samples were obtained from 8 pediatric patients with moderate to severe RTI. Additionally, two nasopharyngeal-aspirate samples from healthy adults were used as control samples (Table 1
). All samples were tested with a multiplex-PCR assay for a panel of respiratory pathogens including respiratory syncytial virus (RSV), influenzavirus-A and B, adenovirus, Mycoplasma pneumoniae, Chlamydophila pneumoniae, bocavirus, parainfluenzavirus 1-4 (PIV), coronavirus OC43 and 229 E, enterovirus, human metapneumovirus (hMPV), and human rhinovirus (hRV). Samples were processed according to the scheme depicted in Fig. 1
.
